snippet.textDisplay:
Beautiful music
My daughters love this a lot. They like to listen to your music every night. It makes them sleep tight and have a sweet dream.
snippet.textOriginal:
Beautiful music
My daughters love this a lot. They like to listen to your music every night. It makes them sleep tight and have a sweet dream.

snippet.textDisplay:
I have listened and pondered over this music for years now. Throughout the years, I have been subjected to some of the worst humanity has to offer. I have been around those whom society would deem vile and beyond redemption. I have lived a harsh life in comparison to most and I have had it easier than some others. Every night I lay down, I put this beautiful music on and transport to a different place and different time. I am taken to a place where I can breathe in peace. No stress, no pain, no living with anxiety or fear, no worries about the future and what it may bring. It has been over two years now and while I am still struggling to know my place in this world, I have a beautiful daughter whom I dote on and love more than this world. We now listen to the same music every night. We now journey together listening to this beautiful music side by side. 

No matter what you may be going through in life, remember that there is always a future. There is always something to look forward to. You might not be able to see it, but your future self will love you for it. Stay strong, Stay healthy, Stay beautiful and Stay alive. 

<3

i wrote this for my best friend.

daisy 
i think that iâ€™ve realised why i loathe myself so much. iâ€™ve always felt useless to the people around me and felt as if nobody had loved me at all. of course, that never changed the fact that i loved others, but that didnâ€™t matter. i understand that youâ€™ve always tried to be a helpful and nurturing friend, but my mind always tried to convince me that it wasnâ€™t genuine. anybody who ever tried to be kind was never genuine. watching you the other day, however, changed my entire point of view. watching you sit there in front of me, teardrops running down your face before they fell from your your cheek, telling me you loved me made me feel..
..well, i canâ€™t quite explain it. 
the whole experience felt so surreal. i never thought iâ€™d hear the words â€˜i love youâ€™ directed towards me by anybody but my own parents. i hope you know that hearing it from a friend, especially from you, has left a great impact. i also hope you realise how amazing of a person you are, in case i havenâ€™t stressed it enough in the past. you have so many amazing qualities and traits, and iâ€™m sure that you have brightened many peopleâ€™s days.
including mine.
hugs feel different from you. i always tell others that i never really feel safe, but in your arms, i feel as though iâ€™ve been pulled into an animated film; nothing disastrous could happen in those moments. and although iâ€™ve never been one for physical affection, iâ€™ve found myself craving those moments when we can pull each other into an embrace. 
itâ€™s funny how much you mean to me, i donâ€™t think iâ€™ve ever quite felt the way i do around you. i feel more comfortable around you than i have with anybody, including parents, phycologists, and even other existing friendships. that truly means a lot to me. your words have done what none of my phycologists (or anybody, for that matter) have ever managed to do.
for once, i have a little hope in myself.

snippet.textDisplay:
One summer day, I was spirited away 
Toes touching ocean waves,
Whispering in my ears tales from earthsea.
I dreamt of a castle in the sky,  
Mononoke Hime, the spirit of the forests beyond,
Wishing that Marnie was here (lol).
In his brilliant plane, Porco Rosso saluted and glided into the
Days of old.
The sunflower house glimmered with the returns of the rondo 
As my neighbor Totoro
Led me down the path of the wind. 
The legends of the wind filled me with wonder,
Reminding me of home, sweet home. I stopped
At a grave of fireflies, flickering with neon melancholy. 
I remembered a summer of goodbye, 
From up on poppy hill. 











(in order of the time stamps)
snippet.textOriginal:
One summer day, I was spirited away 
Toes touching ocean waves,
Whispering in my ears tales from earthsea.
I dreamt of a castle in the sky,  
Mononoke Hime, the spirit of the forests beyond,
Wishing that Marnie was here (lol).
In his brilliant plane, Porco Rosso saluted and glided into the
Days of old.
The sunflower house glimmered with the returns of the rondo 
As my neighbor Totoro
Led me down the path of the wind. 
The legends of the wind filled me with wonder,
Reminding me of home, sweet home. I stopped
At a grave of fireflies, flickering with neon melancholy. 
I remembered a summer of goodbye, 
From up on poppy hill. 











(in order of the time stamps)

snippet.textDisplay:
So personal... Deeply satisfying and soothing, makes me want to cry as I said because it is so personal... I canâ€™t explain what I feel. I used to be obsessed with anime and manga I draw manga and I am second best in my class (I am not trying to brag ), and you know? When I was a beginner, I listen to this music, and it got me creative and emotional and dramatic and that is what you need in art!  And so it got me to second place!
But anyways, now not as much, now I am in The Hobbit, Lord Of The Rings and Tolkien books for I love the movies and plan to read the books. But... just seeing anime wants me to cry or when I listen to this music... Do you know that feeling of a happy memory and you feel so happy? But you know it wonâ€™t come back? And so you have a sad but happy emotion at the same time. When I watch for example, Winderia (it is an old anime movie back in the young 70â€™s and old 80â€™s), I get that feeling as I have, listening to this music... 
We as of people, will never let this die... 
Till it is time to let go, but. Never,
Forget.
